body:
Adds Discord bot support to the SDK and slightly reformats base notification message. Intentionally kept the message template light so that the bulk of it is defined by the Radio per the Radio's requirements.

I combined both Slack and Discord bots into one `bots.rs` file since I imagine a lot of the context around notifications in the future would be shared.

PS should be merged after https://github.com/graphops/poi-radio/pull/56 since the changes from there are merged in this branch for testing.

Example usage:
```
async fn main() {
    let discord_webhook_url = env::var("DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL")
        .expect("Please set the DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL environment variable");
    let slack_token = env::var("SLACK_TOKEN")
        .expect("Please set the SLACK_TOKEN environment variable");
    let slack_channel = env::var("SLACK_CHANNEL")
        .expect("Please set the SLACK_CHANNEL environment variable");

    let radio_name = "My Radio";
    let content = "This is an alert message";

    // Send a Discord notification
    match DiscordBot::send_webhook(&discord_webhook_url, radio_name, content).await {
        Ok(_) => println!("Discord notification sent successfully!"),
        Err(e) => eprintln!("Error sending Discord notification: {}", e),
    }

    // Send a Slack notification
    match SlackBot::send_webhook(slack_token, &slack_channel, radio_name, content).await {
        Ok(_) => println!("Slack notification sent successfully!"),
        Err(e) => eprintln!("Error sending Slack notification: {}", e),
    }
}
```

### Description
For different radio use cases, the structure of the radio payloads inside `GraphcastMessage` must be flexible. This PR allows Radio specific message definitions to be passed in as a generic protobuf `message` field in the `GraphcastMessage`. 

Individual radios are responsible for satisfying 
- [Eip712](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712) standard for message hashing and signing and 
- [Protobuf](https://docs.rs/prost/latest/prost/index.html) types for encoding and decoding during transmission. 

Example Radio message definition
```
    /// Required packages
    use ethers_core::types::transaction::eip712::Eip712;
    use ethers_derive_eip712::*;
    use prost::Message;
    use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};

    /// Auto trait derivations for radio message. Example  with 2 fields
    #[derive(Eip712, EthAbiType, Clone, Message, Serialize, Deserialize)]
    #[eip712(
        name = "Graphcast Test Radio",
        version = "0",
        chain_id = 1,
        verifying_contract = "0xc944e90c64b2c07662a292be6244bdf05cda44a7"
    )]
    pub struct RadioPayloadMessage {
        #[prost(string, tag = "1")]
        pub identifier: String,
        #[prost(string, tag = "2")]
        pub content: String,
    }

    /// Helper functions for construction and extractions, but not necessary since the fields are public
    impl RadioPayloadMessage {
        pub fn new(identifier: String, content: String) -> Self {
            RadioPayloadMessage {
                identifier,
                content,
            }
        }

        pub fn content_string(&self) -> String {
            self.content.clone()
        }
    }
```

